{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1179,"text":"So last year, on the Fourth of July,"},{"time":3523,"text":"experiments at the Large Hadron Collider"},{"time":6022,"text":"discovered the Higgs boson."},{"time":8312,"text":"It was a historical day."},{"time":10280,"text":"There's no doubt that from now on,"},{"time":12575,"text":"the Fourth of July will be remembered"},{"time":14409,"text":"not as the day of the Declaration of Independence,"},{"time":16851,"text":"but as the day of the discovery of the Higgs boson."},{"time":20685,"text":"Well, at least, here at CERN."}]},{"cues":[{"time":23117,"text":"But for me, the biggest surprise of that day"},{"time":27272,"text":"was that there was no big surprise."},{"time":29771,"text":"In the eye of a theoretical physicist,"},{"time":32370,"text":"the Higgs boson is a clever explanation"},{"time":34263,"text":"of how some elementary particles gain mass,"},{"time":37786,"text":"but it seems a fairly unsatisfactory"},{"time":40622,"text":"and incomplete solution."},{"time":42828,"text":"Too many questions are left unanswered."},{"time":45852,"text":"The Higgs boson does not share the beauty,"},{"time":48687,"text":"the symmetry, the elegance,"},{"time":50572,"text":"of the rest of the elementary particle world."},{"time":53300,"text":"For this reason, the majority of theoretical physicists"},{"time":56922,"text":"believe that the Higgs boson could not"},{"time":59864,"text":"be the full story."},{"time":62346,"text":"We were expecting new particles and new phenomena"},{"time":65200,"text":"accompanying the Higgs boson."},{"time":67650,"text":"Instead, so far, the measurements"},{"time":69968,"text":"coming from the LHC show no signs of new particles"},{"time":73726,"text":"or unexpected phenomena."}]},{"cues":[{"time":75875,"text":"Of course, the verdict is not definitive."},{"time":79528,"text":"In 2015, the LHC will almost double"},{"time":83522,"text":"the energy of the colliding protons,"},{"time":86213,"text":"and these more powerful collisions"},{"time":88284,"text":"will allow us to explore further the particle world,"},{"time":92868,"text":"and we will certainly learn much more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96000,"text":"But for the moment, since we have found"},{"time":99146,"text":"no evidence for new phenomena, let us suppose"},{"time":102295,"text":"that the particles that we know today,"},{"time":105459,"text":"including the Higgs boson,"},{"time":107315,"text":"are the only elementary particles in nature,"},{"time":110600,"text":"even at energies much larger"},{"time":113344,"text":"than what we have explored so far."},{"time":116110,"text":"Let's see where this hypothesis is going to lead us."},{"time":120742,"text":"We will find a surprising and intriguing result"},{"time":124174,"text":"about our universe, and to explain my point,"},{"time":127973,"text":"let me first tell you what the Higgs is about,"},{"time":131849,"text":"and to do so, we have to go back"},{"time":134983,"text":"to one tenth of a billionth of a second"},{"time":139340,"text":"after the Big Bang."},{"time":140871,"text":"And according to the Higgs theory,"},{"time":142912,"text":"at that instant, a dramatic event took place"},{"time":146278,"text":"in the universe."},{"time":147869,"text":"Space-time underwent a phase transition."},{"time":152660,"text":"It was something very similar to the phase transition"},{"time":155737,"text":"that occurs when water turns into ice"},{"time":159282,"text":"below zero degrees."},{"time":161243,"text":"But in our case, the phase transition"},{"time":164183,"text":"is not a change in the way the molecules"},{"time":166714,"text":"are arranged inside the material,"},{"time":169000,"text":"but is about a change"},{"time":170888,"text":"of the very fabric of space-time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174514,"text":"During this phase transition, empty space"},{"time":177140,"text":"became filled with a substance"},{"time":179812,"text":"that we now call Higgs field."},{"time":182844,"text":"And this substance may seem invisible to us,"},{"time":185173,"text":"but it has a physical reality."},{"time":187851,"text":"It surrounds us all the time,"},{"time":189909,"text":"just like the air we breathe in this room."},{"time":193610,"text":"And some elementary particles interact"},{"time":195928,"text":"with this substance, gaining energy in the process."},{"time":199756,"text":"And this intrinsic energy is what we call"},{"time":202831,"text":"the mass of a particle,"},{"time":204964,"text":"and by discovering the Higgs boson, the LHC"},{"time":208217,"text":"has conclusively proved that this substance is real,"},{"time":212749,"text":"because it is the stuff the Higgs bosons are made of."},{"time":216668,"text":"And this, in a nutshell, is the essence of the Higgs story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":220112,"text":"But this story is far more interesting than that."},{"time":224855,"text":"By studying the Higgs theory,"},{"time":227166,"text":"theoretical physicists discovered,"},{"time":229526,"text":"not through an experiment"},{"time":231430,"text":"but with the power of mathematics,"},{"time":233906,"text":"that the Higgs field does not necessarily exist"},{"time":237618,"text":"only in the form that we observe today."},{"time":240955,"text":"Just like matter can exist as liquid or solid,"},{"time":246000,"text":"so the Higgs field, the substance that fills all space-time,"},{"time":250572,"text":"could exist in two states."},{"time":253926,"text":"Besides the known Higgs state,"},{"time":256236,"text":"there could be a second state in which the Higgs field"},{"time":259383,"text":"is billions and billions times denser"},{"time":262919,"text":"than what we observe today,"},{"time":264964,"text":"and the mere existence of another state"},{"time":268451,"text":"of the Higgs field poses a potential problem."},{"time":272696,"text":"This is because, according to the laws"},{"time":275934,"text":"of quantum mechanics, it is possible"},{"time":278627,"text":"to have transitions between two states,"},{"time":281459,"text":"even in the presence of an energy barrier"},{"time":284408,"text":"separating the two states,"},{"time":287036,"text":"and the phenomenon is called,"},{"time":289245,"text":"quite appropriately, quantum tunneling."},{"time":293387,"text":"Because of quantum tunneling,"},{"time":295278,"text":"I could disappear from this room"},{"time":297811,"text":"and reappear in the next room,"},{"time":301133,"text":"practically penetrating the wall."},{"time":304528,"text":"But don't expect me to actually perform the trick"},{"time":307343,"text":"in front of your eyes, because the probability"},{"time":309921,"text":"for me to penetrate the wall is ridiculously small."},{"time":314309,"text":"You would have to wait a really long time"},{"time":316907,"text":"before it happens, but believe me,"},{"time":319039,"text":"quantum tunneling is a real phenomenon,"},{"time":322216,"text":"and it has been observed in many systems."},{"time":325411,"text":"For instance, the tunnel diode,"},{"time":327973,"text":"a component used in electronics,"},{"time":330170,"text":"works thanks to the wonders"},{"time":332592,"text":"of quantum tunneling."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334912,"text":"But let's go back to the Higgs field."},{"time":337204,"text":"If the ultra-dense Higgs state existed,"},{"time":341767,"text":"then, because of quantum tunneling,"},{"time":344121,"text":"a bubble of this state could suddenly appear"},{"time":347834,"text":"in a certain place of the universe at a certain time,"},{"time":351076,"text":"and it is analogous to what happens when you boil water."},{"time":354841,"text":"Bubbles of vapor form inside the water,"},{"time":357930,"text":"then they expand, turning liquid into gas."},{"time":361786,"text":"In the same way, a bubble of the ultra-dense Higgs state"},{"time":366590,"text":"could come into existence because of quantum tunneling."},{"time":370017,"text":"The bubble would then expand at the speed of light,"},{"time":372854,"text":"invading all space, and turning the Higgs field"},{"time":376340,"text":"from the familiar state into a new state."}]},{"cues":[{"time":379989,"text":"Is this a problem? Yes, it's a big a problem."},{"time":384150,"text":"We may not realize it in ordinary life,"},{"time":386895,"text":"but the intensity of the Higgs field is critical"},{"time":390100,"text":"for the structure of matter."},{"time":392745,"text":"If the Higgs field were only a few times more intense,"},{"time":396818,"text":"we would see atoms shrinking, neutrons decaying"},{"time":399762,"text":"inside atomic nuclei, nuclei disintegrating,"},{"time":403448,"text":"and hydrogen would be"},{"time":405788,"text":"the only possible chemical element in the universe."},{"time":410140,"text":"And the Higgs field, in the ultra-dense Higgs state,"},{"time":413151,"text":"is not just a few times more intense than today,"},{"time":416965,"text":"but billions of times,"},{"time":419160,"text":"and if space-time were filled by this Higgs state,"},{"time":422362,"text":"all atomic matter would collapse."},{"time":425515,"text":"No molecular structures would be possible, no life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":430005,"text":"So, I wonder, is it possible"},{"time":433343,"text":"that in the future, the Higgs field"},{"time":435929,"text":"will undergo a phase transition and,"},{"time":438494,"text":"through quantum tunneling, will be transformed"},{"time":441623,"text":"into this nasty, ultra-dense state?"},{"time":446310,"text":"In other words, I ask myself, what is the fate"},{"time":449835,"text":"of the Higgs field in our universe?"},{"time":452918,"text":"And the crucial ingredient necessary"},{"time":455169,"text":"to answer this question is the Higgs boson mass."},{"time":459555,"text":"And experiments at the LHC found that the mass"},{"time":463666,"text":"of the Higgs boson is about 126 GeV."},{"time":467940,"text":"This is tiny when expressed in familiar units,"},{"time":470976,"text":"because it's equal to something like"},{"time":472296,"text":"10 to the minus 22 grams,"},{"time":474503,"text":"but it is large in particle physics units,"},{"time":478473,"text":"because it is equal to the weight"},{"time":480577,"text":"of an entire molecule"},{"time":482823,"text":"of a DNA constituent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":485243,"text":"So armed with this information from the LHC,"},{"time":488630,"text":"together with some colleagues here at CERN,"},{"time":490574,"text":"we computed the probability"},{"time":492483,"text":"that our universe could quantum tunnel"},{"time":495498,"text":"into the ultra-dense Higgs state,"},{"time":498616,"text":"and we found a very intriguing result."},{"time":502293,"text":"Our calculations showed"},{"time":504442,"text":"that the measured value of the Higgs boson mass"},{"time":507614,"text":"is very special."},{"time":509459,"text":"It has just the right value"},{"time":512378,"text":"to keep the universe hanging"},{"time":515071,"text":"in an unstable situation."},{"time":517641,"text":"The Higgs field is in a wobbly configuration"},{"time":520897,"text":"that has lasted so far"},{"time":522946,"text":"but that will eventually collapse."},{"time":525991,"text":"So according to these calculations,"},{"time":529170,"text":"we are like campers"},{"time":531200,"text":"who accidentally set their tent"},{"time":533652,"text":"at the edge of a cliff."},{"time":535446,"text":"And eventually, the Higgs field"},{"time":537236,"text":"will undergo a phase transition"},{"time":539172,"text":"and matter will collapse into itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":542216,"text":"So is this how humanity is going to disappear?"},{"time":545660,"text":"I don't think so."},{"time":547415,"text":"Our calculation shows that quantum tunneling"},{"time":550768,"text":"of the Higgs field is not likely to occur"},{"time":554424,"text":"in the next 10 to the 100 years,"},{"time":557928,"text":"and this is a very long time."},{"time":560970,"text":"It's even longer than"},{"time":562738,"text":"the time it takes for Italy to form a stable government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":566407,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":568814,"text":"Even so, we will be long gone by then."},{"time":572605,"text":"In about five billion years,"},{"time":575213,"text":"our sun will become a red giant,"},{"time":577670,"text":"as large as the Earth's orbit,"},{"time":580183,"text":"and our Earth will be kaput,"},{"time":583460,"text":"and in a thousand billion years,"},{"time":585817,"text":"if dark energy keeps on fueling"},{"time":588103,"text":"space expansion at the present rate,"},{"time":590938,"text":"you will not even be able to see as far as your toes,"},{"time":595115,"text":"because everything around you"},{"time":596812,"text":"expands at a rate faster than the speed of light."},{"time":600513,"text":"So it is really unlikely"},{"time":602498,"text":"that we will be around to see the Higgs field collapse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":606368,"text":"But the reason why I am interested"},{"time":609947,"text":"in the transition of the Higgs field"},{"time":611959,"text":"is because I want to address the question,"},{"time":615244,"text":"why is the Higgs boson mass so special?"},{"time":620209,"text":"Why is it just right to keep the universe"},{"time":623183,"text":"at the edge of a phase transition?"},{"time":626673,"text":"Theoretical physicists always ask \"why\" questions."},{"time":630535,"text":"More than how a phenomenon works,"},{"time":633210,"text":"theoretical physicists are always interested in"},{"time":635682,"text":"why a phenomenon works in the way it works."},{"time":638914,"text":"We think that this these \"why\" questions"},{"time":642276,"text":"can give us clues"},{"time":643999,"text":"about the fundamental principles of nature."},{"time":647537,"text":"And indeed, a possible answer to my question"},{"time":651442,"text":"opens up new universes, literally."},{"time":655806,"text":"It has been speculated that our universe"},{"time":659247,"text":"is only a bubble in a soapy multiverse"},{"time":663380,"text":"made out of a multitude of bubbles,"},{"time":665943,"text":"and each bubble is a different universe"},{"time":668159,"text":"with different fundamental constants"},{"time":670053,"text":"and different physical laws."},{"time":671918,"text":"And in this context, you can only talk about"},{"time":673924,"text":"the probability of finding a certain value of the Higgs mass."},{"time":678635,"text":"Then the key to the mystery"},{"time":680978,"text":"could lie in the statistical properties"},{"time":684241,"text":"of the multiverse."},{"time":686469,"text":"It would be something like what happens"},{"time":688883,"text":"with sand dunes on a beach."},{"time":691120,"text":"In principle, you could imagine to find sand dunes"},{"time":693992,"text":"of any slope angle in a beach,"},{"time":696422,"text":"and yet, the slope angles of sand dunes"},{"time":700583,"text":"are typically around 30, 35 degrees."},{"time":704053,"text":"And the reason is simple:"},{"time":705721,"text":"because wind builds up the sand, gravity makes it fall."},{"time":709399,"text":"As a result, the vast majority of sand dunes"},{"time":712283,"text":"have slope angles around the critical value,"},{"time":716202,"text":"near to collapse."},{"time":718186,"text":"And something similar could happen"},{"time":721183,"text":"for the Higgs boson mass in the multiverse."},{"time":725720,"text":"In the majority of bubble universes,"},{"time":728592,"text":"the Higgs mass could be around the critical value,"},{"time":731649,"text":"near to a cosmic collapse of the Higgs field,"},{"time":735245,"text":"because of two competing effects,"},{"time":737192,"text":"just as in the case of sand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":740778,"text":"My story does not have an end,"},{"time":743923,"text":"because we still don't know the end of the story."},{"time":747658,"text":"This is science in progress,"},{"time":750946,"text":"and to solve the mystery, we need more data,"},{"time":754780,"text":"and hopefully, the LHC will soon add new clues"},{"time":759396,"text":"to this story."},{"time":762017,"text":"Just one number, the Higgs boson mass,"},{"time":765847,"text":"and yet, out of this number we learn so much."},{"time":771176,"text":"I started from a hypothesis, that the known particles"},{"time":774223,"text":"are all there is in the universe,"},{"time":776259,"text":"even beyond the domain explored so far."},{"time":778965,"text":"From this, we discovered that the Higgs field"},{"time":782733,"text":"that permeates space-time may be standing"},{"time":786176,"text":"on a knife edge, ready for cosmic collapse,"},{"time":790733,"text":"and we discovered that this may be a hint"},{"time":794283,"text":"that our universe is only a grain of sand"},{"time":798316,"text":"in a giant beach, the multiverse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":801929,"text":"But I don't know if my hypothesis is right."},{"time":805180,"text":"That's how physics works: A single measurement"},{"time":808863,"text":"can put us on the road to a new understanding"},{"time":811727,"text":"of the universe"},{"time":813390,"text":"or it can send us down a blind alley."},{"time":816409,"text":"But whichever it turns out to be,"},{"time":818973,"text":"there is one thing I'm sure of:"},{"time":822165,"text":"The journey will be full of surprises."}]},{"cues":[{"time":825514,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":826887,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}